org.jlinalg

Class FieldElement<RE extends IRingElement<RE>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jlinalg.RingElement<RE>
      • org.jlinalg.FieldElement<RE>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<RE>, IRingElement<RE>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BigDecimalWrapper, Complex, DoubleWrapper, F2, FastRational, FieldP, Rational, RationalFunction

    public abstract class FieldElement<RE extends IRingElement<RE>>
extends RingElement<RE>
implements IRingElement<RE>
    This class represents an element of an arbitrary field. It has to have four operations (add, subtract, multiply, divide) a neutral element of addition (zero) and a neutral element of multiplication (one). Concrete number types (fields) can be easily implemented by extending this class.
    Note! Performance Issue
    Most non abstract methods in this class were only implemented to make the process of implementing a new FieldElement convenient and short. These methods should be overwritten, whenever one is more interested in performance than in just getting something that works.

    Note! FieldElements are presumably immutable. Extensions to this class should not allow a modification after instantiation!

    Author:
    Andreas Keilhauer, Simon D. Levy
